cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as semantic segmentation, object detection, and scene classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which makes it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to object localization, which could be relevant to cs.RO (Robotics) as well. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a dataset, which could make it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
